What do you see in this code?

orb Crystal { position: [0,2,0], color: "#00ffff" }
orb Crystal2 { position: [3,2,0], color: "#ff00ff" }

Now we're talking! Let me draw the flow:

```
[Crystal] ←──click──→ [Crystal2]
    │                      │
    └── toggles color ─────┘
```

Bidirectional connection:

```holo
orb Crystal { 
  position: [0,2,0]
  color: "#00ffff"
  traits: ["interactive"]
  partner: "Crystal2"
}

orb Crystal2 { 
  position: [3,2,0]
  color: "#ff00ff"
  traits: ["interactive"]
  partner: "Crystal"
}

logic {
  on_interact("Crystal") {
    Crystal2.pulse()
    Crystal2.color = random_color()
  }

  on_interact("Crystal2") {
    Crystal.pulse()
    Crystal.color = random_color()
  }
}
```

Now clicking either crystal affects its partner - they're linked!

Classic puzzle! Let me map the flow:

```
[Switch1] ──on/off──┐
                    │
[Switch2] ──on/off──┼──→ [All On?] ──yes──→ [Door Opens]
                    │        │
[Switch3] ──on/off──┘       no
                             │
                             └──→ [Door Stays Locked]
```

Convergent flow - multiple inputs, one output:

```holo
composition "Switch Puzzle" {

  // The switches (input nodes)
  orb Switch1 {
    position: [-2, 1, 0]
    state: "off"
    traits: ["interactive", "toggle"]
  }

  orb Switch2 {
    position: [0, 1, 0]
    state: "off"
    traits: ["interactive", "toggle"]
  }

  orb Switch3 {
    position: [2, 1, 0]
    state: "off"
    traits: ["interactive", "toggle"]
  }

  // The door (output node)
  orb Door {
    position: [0, 0, 5]
    state: "locked"
    traits: ["door"]
  }

  logic {
    // Each switch toggles and checks the puzzle
    on_interact("Switch1") {
      Switch1.state = toggle(Switch1.state)
      Switch1.play_sound(Switch1.state)
      check_puzzle()
    }

    on_interact("Switch2") {
      Switch2.state = toggle(Switch2.state)
      Switch2.play_sound(Switch2.state)
      check_puzzle()
    }

    on_interact("Switch3") {
      Switch3.state = toggle(Switch3.state)
      Switch3.play_sound(Switch3.state)
      check_puzzle()
    }

    // The convergence point
    function check_puzzle() {
      if (Switch1.state == "on" && 
          Switch2.state == "on" && 
          Switch3.state == "on") {
        Door.unlock()
        Door.open()
        audio.play("puzzle_solved")
        ui.toast("The door opens!")
      }
    }
  }
}
```

All three must be ON for the door to open. The flow converges at check_puzzle().

Dominoes are a **linear chain flow** - each node triggers the next:

```
[Push] ──→ [D1] ──→ [D2] ──→ [D3] ──→ [D4] ──→ [D5] ──→ [End Effect]
            │        │        │        │        │
           fall    fall     fall     fall     fall
```

Here's how to build it:

```holo
composition "Domino Chain" {

  template "Domino" {
    state { fallen: false }

    action fall() {
      if (this.fallen) return  // Can't fall twice

      this.fallen = true
      this.animate("topple")
      audio.play_at("domino_click", this.position)

      // Trigger the next one after a delay
      if (this.next) {
        after(200) {
          this.next.fall()
        }
      }
    }
  }

  spatial_group "DominoLine" {
    object "D1" using "Domino" { position: [0, 0, 0], next: "D2" }
    object "D2" using "Domino" { position: [0.5, 0, 0], next: "D3" }
    object "D3" using "Domino" { position: [1.0, 0, 0], next: "D4" }
    object "D4" using "Domino" { position: [1.5, 0, 0], next: "D5" }
    object "D5" using "Domino" { position: [2.0, 0, 0], next: null }
  }

  // The starting trigger
  orb StartButton {
    position: [-1, 1, 0]
    traits: ["interactive"]
  }

  logic {
    on_interact("StartButton") {
      D1.fall()  // Start the chain!
    }

    // End effect when last domino falls
    on_fallen("D5") {
      spawn_particles("celebration", D5.position)
      ui.toast("Chain complete!")
    }
  }
}
```

**The flow propagates:**
```
[Button] ──click──→ D1.fall() ──200ms──→ D2.fall() ──200ms──→ ...
```

Each domino knows its `next` neighbor - that's the edge in the graph. The delay creates the cascade effect.

Dialogue trees are **branching graphs** - one input, multiple possible outputs:

```
                    [Start]
                       │
                    "Hello"
                       │
              ┌────────┴────────┐
              │                 │
         [Ask about]      [Ask for help]
          the town              │
              │                 │
      ┌───────┼───────┐    [Give quest]
      │       │       │         │
   [Shop]  [Inn]  [Danger]   [Accept]
      │       │       │      /     \
      ↓       ↓       ↓   [Yes]   [No]
```

Here's the .holo:

```holo
composition "NPC Dialogue" {

  // Dialogue data structure (the graph)
  const dialogue_tree = {
    "start": {
      speaker: "Merchant",
      text: "Welcome, traveler! What brings you to our village?",
      choices: [
        { text: "Tell me about this town.", next: "about_town" },
        { text: "I need help with something.", next: "need_help" },
        { text: "Just passing through.", next: "goodbye" }
      ]
    },
    "about_town": {
      speaker: "Merchant",
      text: "Ah, Willowbrook! We have the finest market in the region.",
      choices: [
        { text: "Where's the shop?", next: "shop_info" },
        { text: "Is there an inn?", next: "inn_info" },
        { text: "Any dangers nearby?", next: "danger_info" },
        { text: "Thanks, goodbye.", next: "goodbye" }
      ]
    },
    "need_help": {
      speaker: "Merchant",
      text: "Help? Well... there is one thing. Wolves have been attacking our sheep.",
      choices: [
        { text: "I'll handle it!", next: "accept_quest" },
        { text: "Sorry, not my problem.", next: "refuse_quest" }
      ]
    },
    "accept_quest": {
      speaker: "Merchant",
      text: "Thank you! Kill 5 wolves and I'll reward you handsomely.",
      action: () => { Quest.start("wolf_hunt") },
      choices: [
        { text: "Consider it done.", next: "goodbye" }
      ]
    },
    "refuse_quest": {
      speaker: "Merchant",
      text: "I understand. Safe travels then.",
      action: () => { Player.reputation["merchant"] -= 5 },
      choices: [
        { text: "Goodbye.", next: "goodbye" }
      ]
    },
    "goodbye": {
      speaker: "Merchant",
      text: "Farewell, traveler!",
      end: true
    }
  }

  object "Merchant" using "NPC" {
    position: [5, 0, 3]
    traits: ["talkable"]
    dialogue: "start"  // Entry point into the tree
  }

  logic {
    on_interact("Merchant") {
      DialogueUI.start(dialogue_tree, Merchant.dialogue)
    }

    on_dialogue_choice(choice) {
      // Execute any action
      if (choice.action) choice.action()

      // Navigate to next node
      if (choice.next) {
        DialogueUI.show(dialogue_tree[choice.next])
      }

      // Check for end
      if (dialogue_tree[choice.next].end) {
        DialogueUI.close()
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**Visualizing the player's path:**
```
Player clicked "I need help" → "need_help" node
Player clicked "I'll handle it!" → "accept_quest" node → Quest started!
Player clicked "Consider it done." → "goodbye" node → Dialogue ends
```

Each choice is an edge leading to another node.

Inventory is a **container graph** - slots hold items, items have properties:

```
[Inventory]
     │
     ├── [Slot 0] ── contains ── [Sword]
     │                              └── damage: 10
     │
     ├── [Slot 1] ── contains ── [Potion] x3
     │                              └── heals: 25
     │
     ├── [Slot 2] ── empty
     │
     └── [Slot 3] ── contains ── [Key]
                                    └── opens: "chest_01"
```

**Flows:**
```
[Pickup] ──→ find empty slot ──→ [add item]
[Use] ──→ trigger item effect ──→ [remove/decrement]
[Drop] ──→ spawn in world ──→ [remove from slot]
```

```holo
composition "Inventory System" {

  template "InventorySlot" {
    state {
      item: null
      count: 0
    }

    action add(item_data, amount = 1) {
      if (this.item == null) {
        this.item = item_data
        this.count = amount
      } else if (this.item.id == item_data.id && item_data.stackable) {
        this.count += amount
      } else {
        return false  // Slot occupied
      }
      return true
    }

    action remove(amount = 1) {
      this.count -= amount
      if (this.count <= 0) {
        this.item = null
        this.count = 0
      }
    }

    action use() {
      if (this.item && this.item.usable) {
        this.item.onUse()
        if (this.item.consumable) {
          this.remove(1)
        }
      }
    }
  }

  // Player inventory (8 slots)
  spatial_group "PlayerInventory" {
    object "Slot_0" using "InventorySlot" {}
    object "Slot_1" using "InventorySlot" {}
    object "Slot_2" using "InventorySlot" {}
    object "Slot_3" using "InventorySlot" {}
    object "Slot_4" using "InventorySlot" {}
    object "Slot_5" using "InventorySlot" {}
    object "Slot_6" using "InventorySlot" {}
    object "Slot_7" using "InventorySlot" {}
  }

  // Item definitions
  const Items = {
    "health_potion": {
      id: "health_potion",
      name: "Health Potion",
      icon: "potion_red",
      stackable: true,
      usable: true,
      consumable: true,
      onUse: () => { Player.health += 25 }
    },
    "iron_sword": {
      id: "iron_sword",
      name: "Iron Sword",
      icon: "sword_iron",
      stackable: false,
      equippable: true,
      slot: "weapon",
      stats: { damage: 10 }
    }
  }

  logic {
    // Pickup flow: World Item → Inventory
    on_collect(item) {
      let added = false
      for (slot in PlayerInventory) {
        if (slot.add(Items[item.type])) {
          added = true
          despawn(item)
          ui.toast("Picked up " + item.name)
          break
        }
      }
      if (!added) {
        ui.toast("Inventory full!")
      }
    }

    // Use flow: Slot → Effect
    on_inventory_use(slot_index) {
      let slot = PlayerInventory["Slot_" + slot_index]
      slot.use()
    }

    // Drop flow: Slot → World
    on_inventory_drop(slot_index) {
      let slot = PlayerInventory["Slot_" + slot_index]
      if (slot.item) {
        spawn(slot.item.id, Player.position + [0, 0.5, 1])
        slot.remove(1)
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**The complete item lifecycle:**
```
[World Item] ──pickup──→ [Inventory Slot] ──use──→ [Effect Applied]
                              │
                              └──drop──→ [World Item]
```

Crafting is a **recipe graph** - multiple inputs combine into one output:

```
[Iron Ore] ──┐
             │
[Iron Ore] ──┼──→ [Furnace] ──→ [Iron Bar]
             │
[Coal] ──────┘


[Iron Bar] ──┐
             │
[Iron Bar] ──┼──→ [Anvil] ──→ [Iron Sword]
             │
[Wood] ──────┘
```

**The pattern: Many-to-One transformation**

```holo
composition "Crafting System" {

  // Recipe definitions (the transformation rules)
  const Recipes = {
    "iron_bar": {
      station: "furnace",
      inputs: [
        { item: "iron_ore", count: 2 },
        { item: "coal", count: 1 }
      ],
      output: { item: "iron_bar", count: 1 },
      time: 3  // seconds
    },
    "iron_sword": {
      station: "anvil",
      inputs: [
        { item: "iron_bar", count: 2 },
        { item: "wood", count: 1 }
      ],
      output: { item: "iron_sword", count: 1 },
      time: 5
    },
    "health_potion": {
      station: "alchemy_table",
      inputs: [
        { item: "red_herb", count: 2 },
        { item: "water_bottle", count: 1 }
      ],
      output: { item: "health_potion", count: 1 },
      time: 2
    }
  }

  // Crafting stations (the transformation nodes)
  template "CraftingStation" {
    state {
      type: ""
      crafting: false
      progress: 0
      current_recipe: null
    }

    action can_craft(recipe_id) {
      let recipe = Recipes[recipe_id]
      if (recipe.station != this.type) return false

      // Check all ingredients
      for (input in recipe.inputs) {
        if (!Player.hasItem(input.item, input.count)) {
          return false
        }
      }
      return true
    }

    action start_craft(recipe_id) {
      if (!this.can_craft(recipe_id)) return

      let recipe = Recipes[recipe_id]

      // Consume inputs
      for (input in recipe.inputs) {
        Player.removeItem(input.item, input.count)
      }

      // Start crafting
      this.crafting = true
      this.current_recipe = recipe
      this.progress = 0
    }
  }

  spatial_group "CraftingArea" {
    object "Furnace" using "CraftingStation" {
      position: [5, 0, 0]
      type: "furnace"
      traits: ["interactive"]
    }

    object "Anvil" using "CraftingStation" {
      position: [7, 0, 0]
      type: "anvil"
      traits: ["interactive"]
    }

    object "AlchemyTable" using "CraftingStation" {
      position: [9, 0, 0]
      type: "alchemy_table"
      traits: ["interactive"]
    }
  }

  logic {
    // Open crafting UI
    on_interact(station) where station.type in ["furnace", "anvil", "alchemy_table"] {
      let available = get_recipes_for_station(station.type)
      CraftingUI.open(station, available)
    }

    // Start crafting from UI
    on_craft_start(station, recipe_id) {
      station.start_craft(recipe_id)
    }

    // Progress crafting
    every(100) {
      for (station in CraftingStations) {
        if (station.crafting) {
          station.progress += 0.1

          if (station.progress >= station.current_recipe.time) {
            // Crafting complete!
            let output = station.current_recipe.output
            Player.addItem(output.item, output.count)

            station.crafting = false
            station.current_recipe = null

            ui.toast("Crafted: " + output.item)
            audio.play("craft_complete")
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**Recipe as a graph transformation:**
```
BEFORE:                          AFTER:
[Player Inventory]               [Player Inventory]
├── Iron Ore x2  ─────┐          ├── Iron Bar x1  ← NEW!
├── Coal x1      ─────┼──→       └── (ore & coal consumed)
└── Wood x5           │
                      ↓
                 [Furnace]
                 (3 seconds)
```

Stealth is about **detection flows** - multiple senses feeding into an alert state:

```
                    [Player]
                    /      \
               visible?   audible?
                  /          \
                 ↓            ↓
           [Vision Cone]  [Sound Radius]
                  \          /
                   \        /
                    ↓      ↓
               [Detection Meter]
                       │
              ┌────────┼────────┐
              │        │        │
           <30%     30-70%     >70%
              │        │        │
              ↓        ↓        ↓
          [Unaware] [Suspicious] [Alert!]
              │        │           │
           patrol   investigate   chase
```

```holo
composition "Stealth System" {

  template "Guard" {
    state {
      // Senses
      vision_range: 15
      vision_angle: 60  // degrees
      hearing_range: 10

      // Detection
      detection: 0  // 0-100
      alert_state: "unaware"  // unaware, suspicious, alert
      last_known_pos: null
    }

    // Check if player is in vision cone
    action can_see_player() {
      let dist = distance(this.position, Player.position)
      if (dist > this.vision_range) return false

      // Check angle
      let angle_to_player = angle_between(this.forward, Player.position - this.position)
      if (angle_to_player > this.vision_angle / 2) return false

      // Check line of sight (no walls)
      if (raycast_blocked(this.position, Player.position)) return false

      return true
    }

    // Check if player made noise
    action can_hear_player() {
      let dist = distance(this.position, Player.position)
      let noise = Player.current_noise_level

      // Noise travels less far when quiet
      let effective_range = this.hearing_range * noise
      return dist < effective_range
    }

    // State transitions
    action update_alert() {
      if (this.detection < 30) {
        if (this.alert_state != "unaware") {
          this.alert_state = "unaware"
          this.last_known_pos = null
        }
      } else if (this.detection < 70) {
        if (this.alert_state != "suspicious") {
          this.alert_state = "suspicious"
          this.show_indicator("?")
        }
      } else {
        if (this.alert_state != "alert") {
          this.alert_state = "alert"
          this.show_indicator("!")
          this.last_known_pos = Player.position
          audio.play("alert_sound")
        }
      }
    }
  }

  // The player's stealth properties
  template "StealthPlayer" {
    state {
      crouching: false
      moving: false
      in_shadow: false
      current_noise_level: 0  // 0-1
      visibility: 1  // 0-1
    }

    action update_stealth() {
      // Calculate noise
      if (!this.moving) {
        this.current_noise_level = 0
      } else if (this.crouching) {
        this.current_noise_level = 0.3
      } else {
        this.current_noise_level = 0.7
      }

      // Running is louder
      if (Input.get("sprint")) {
        this.current_noise_level = 1.0
      }

      // Calculate visibility
      if (this.in_shadow) {
        this.visibility = 0.3
      } else if (this.crouching) {
        this.visibility = 0.6
      } else {
        this.visibility = 1.0
      }
    }
  }

  spatial_group "Level" {
    object "Player" using "StealthPlayer" {
      position: [0, 0, 0]
    }

    object "Guard_1" using "Guard" {
      position: [10, 0, 5]
      patrol_route: ["wp_a", "wp_b", "wp_c"]
    }

    object "Guard_2" using "Guard" {
      position: [20, 0, 10]
      patrol_route: ["wp_d", "wp_e"]
    }

    // Shadow zones
    orb Shadow_1 { position: [5, 0, 3], radius: 3, traits: ["shadow_zone"] }
    orb Shadow_2 { position: [15, 0, 8], radius: 4, traits: ["shadow_zone"] }
  }

  logic {
    // Player stealth update
    every(100) {
      Player.moving = Player.velocity.length() > 0.1
      Player.in_shadow = is_in_shadow_zone(Player.position)
      Player.update_stealth()
    }

    // Guard detection loop
    every(100) {
      for (guard in Guards) {
        let see = guard.can_see_player()
        let hear = guard.can_hear_player()

        // Detection builds up or decays
        if (see) {
          // Vision detection rate based on visibility
          guard.detection += 5 * Player.visibility
        }
        if (hear) {
          guard.detection += 3 * Player.current_noise_level
        }
        if (!see && !hear) {
          // Slowly forget
          guard.detection -= 2
        }

        // Clamp
        guard.detection = clamp(guard.detection, 0, 100)

        // Update state
        guard.update_alert()
      }
    }

    // Guard behavior based on state
    every(100) {
      for (guard in Guards) {
        match guard.alert_state {
          "unaware" => guard.patrol()
          "suspicious" => guard.investigate(guard.last_known_pos || Player.position)
          "alert" => guard.chase(Player)
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**The detection flow:**
```
[Player Actions]          [Environment]
     │                         │
  moving?                  in shadow?
  running?                     │
  crouching?                   ↓
     │                    [visibility]
     ↓                         │
[noise level]                  │
     │                         │
     └────────┬────────────────┘
              ↓
         [Guard Senses]
         /           \
    vision         hearing
        \           /
         ↓         ↓
       [Detection Meter]
              │
              ↓
     [Alert State Machine]
     unaware → suspicious → alert
```

What's wrong with this scene?

composition "Broken" {
  orb Enemy { position: [0,0,0], health: 100 }
  orb Sword { position: [2,0,0], damage: 25 }

  logic {
    on_attack() {
      Enemy.health -= Sword.damage
    }
  }
}

I see the problem! Let me draw what you have:

```
[Enemy]     [Sword]     [on_attack]
   ○           ○             ?
 health      damage      trigger from where?
```

**Three issues:**

1. **`on_attack()` has no source** - Who/what triggers the attack? The event is floating with no connection.

2. **Sword is an orb, not equipped** - It's just sitting in the world. There's no connection showing the player USING the sword.

3. **No player node** - Who's attacking? The flow is:
   ```
   [???] ──attack──→ [Enemy]
   ```
   The source is missing!

**Fixed version:**

```holo
composition "Fixed Combat" {
  // The player (the attacker)
  orb Player {
    position: [0, 0, -5]
    equipped_weapon: "Sword"  // Connection to sword
  }

  // The enemy (the target)  
  orb Enemy { 
    position: [0, 0, 0]
    health: 100
    traits: ["attackable"]  // Can receive attacks
  }

  // The weapon (a data node, or could be equippable item)
  orb Sword { 
    position: [2, 0, 0]
    damage: 25
    traits: ["weapon", "pickupable"]
  }

  logic {
    // Pickup flow: Player → Sword
    on_interact("Sword") {
      Player.equipped_weapon = Sword
      Sword.visible = false  // Now "held"
      ui.toast("Equipped Sword!")
    }

    // Attack flow: Player → Enemy (using equipped weapon)
    on_player_attack(target) {
      if (target.traits.includes("attackable") && Player.equipped_weapon) {
        let damage = Player.equipped_weapon.damage
        target.health -= damage

        ui.show_damage(damage, target.position)
        audio.play("sword_hit")

        if (target.health <= 0) {
          emit("enemy_died", target)
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

**Now the graph is complete:**
```
[Player] ──equips──→ [Sword]
    │                   │
    │                damage: 25
    │                   │
    └──attacks with────→│
                        ↓
                    [Enemy]
                    health -= 25
```

Every action has a source, every effect has a target, and all the connections are explicit!

Save/Load is about **serializing the graph state** and restoring it:

```
SAVE:                              LOAD:
[Game State Graph]                 [Save File]
        │                               │
   serialize                       deserialize
        │                               │
        ↓                               ↓
   [Save File]                  [Game State Graph]
                                (restored exactly)
```

**What to save:**
```
[Save Data]
├── Player
│   ├── position: [x, y, z]
│   ├── health: 85
│   ├── inventory: [...]
│   └── quests: {...}
│
├── World State
│   ├── opened_chests: ["chest_1", "chest_5"]
│   ├── killed_enemies: ["goblin_3"]
│   └── unlocked_doors: ["door_east"]
│
└── NPCs
    ├── merchant: { dialogue_state: "introduced" }
    └── guard: { quest_given: true }
```

